510static void RigidBodyTree_forwardKinematics(n_robotics_manip_internal_Rig_T *obj,

516  };

884static void kinsim_emxEnsureCapacity_real_T(emxArray_real_T_kinsim_2link__T



885  *emxArray, int32_T oldNumel)



886{



887  int32_T newNumel;



888  int32_T i;



889  void *newData;



890  if (oldNumel < 0) {



891    oldNumel = 0;



892  }



893



894  newNumel = 1;



895  for (i = 0; i < emxArray->numDimensions; i++) {



896    newNumel *= emxArray->size[i];



897  }



898



899  if (newNumel > emxArray->allocatedSize) {



900    i = emxArray->allocatedSize;



901    if (i < 16) {



902      i = 16;



903    }



904



905    while (i < newNumel) {



906      if (i > 1073741823) {



907        i = MAX_int32_T;



908      } else {



909        i <<= 1;



910      }



911    }



912



913    newData = calloc(static_cast<uint32_T>(i), sizeof(real_T));



914    if (emxArray->data != NULL) {



915      memcpy(newData, emxArray->data, sizeof(real_T) * oldNumel);



916      if (emxArray->canFreeData) {



917        free(emxArray->data);



918      }



919    }



920



921    emxArray->data = (real_T *)newData;



922    emxArray->allocatedSize = i;



923    emxArray->canFreeData = true;



924  }



925}
